               <head>Ādāb al-ṣāliḥīn by ʻAbd al-Ḥaqq Dihlavī</head>
               <msContents
                  class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh91005357 https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2008104964">
                  <summary>A Persian Sufi treatise on moral life and etiquette named <title>Ādāb
                        al-Ṣāliḥīn</title> (<title xml:lang="per">آداب الصّالحین</title>) written by
                     ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq ibn Sayf al-Dīn Qādirī Dihlavī (1551-1642) and arranged in 7
                     chapters (<hi rend="italic">bāb</hi>. </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_905-item1">
                     <author key="viaf_45690112">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq ibn Sayf al-Dīn Qādirī
                           Dihlavī </persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">عبدالحقّ ابن سیف الدّین قادری دهلوی </persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23464">Ādāb al-Ṣāliḥīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">آداب الصّالحین </title>
                     <colophon> Copied by <persName role="scr">Ṣādiq al-iʿtiqād Muḥammad Ṣadiq.
                        </persName>
                     </colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p>The author states that his work is almost entirely translated from the
                           chapter <title>Muʿāmalāt</title> (deals and affairs) of <persName
                              role="ant" key="viaf_31996761">al-Ghazzālī's</persName>
                           <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2998">Iḥyāʾ ʿUlūm
                           al-Dīn</title>. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <extent>ff.i+185 <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>165</height>
                              <width>105</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>118</height>
